    <h4>1 comment</h4>
    <div class="comment-box">
      <h5>Bob Douglas <span>Fri 16 Aug at 1:12 pm</span> </h5>
      <p>Callaghan and the Labour leadership were certainly too scared to make any reforms and the Conservatives have the same issue over the NHS (they opposed it after all). The recent winters show how getting it wrong or not being prepared can lead to issues of food shortages, even horsemeat. Thatcher&#39;s attitude to sport is double-edged, her light-handed treatment towards South Africa and the Gleneagles Agreement whilst the Government later tried to stop British athletes attending the Moscow Olympics by taking away their passports and even trying to stop top British athletes training time off from their public service jobs and her attempts to politicise the Olympics.</p>
